# Browser Automation — Toon

## When to Use
- Chrome Extension, browser automation, web scraping, form filling
- Playwright / Puppeteer / CDP integration
- Extract web content → route to kinhluan skills
- "Tự động hóa trình duyệt", "mở rộng Chrome", "cào dữ liệu"

## Chrome Extension (Manifest V3)

### Components
| Component | Context | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|---------|
| Popup | User click | Skill browser, search, settings |
| Content Script | Page DOM | Extract data, inject automation |
| Service Worker | Background | Fetch, cache, messaging |

### Permission Minimization
- Start with `activeTab` + `storage` + `scripting`
- Add `host_permissions` only for specific domains
- Never inject remote scripts

## Content Extraction

### Article Extraction
```typescript
function extractArticle() {
  const title = document.title;
  const candidates = document.querySelectorAll('article, main, [role="main"]');
  const content = candidates[0]?.innerText?.trim() || document.body.innerText.slice(0, 8000);
  return { title, content, url: location.href };
}
```

### Structured Data
```typescript
const jsonLd = [...document.querySelectorAll('script[type="application/ld+json"]')]
  .map(s => JSON.parse(s.textContent || '{}'));
```

### Tables
```typescript
const tables = [...document.querySelectorAll('table')].map(t => ({
  headers: [...t.querySelectorAll('th')].map(th => th.innerText.trim()),
  rows: [...t.querySelectorAll('tr')].map(tr =>
    [...tr.querySelectorAll('td')].map(td => td.innerText.trim())
  ).filter(r => r.length)
}));
```

## UI Automation

### Playwright
```typescript
import { chromium } from 'playwright';
const browser = await chromium.launch();
const page = await browser.newPage();
await page.goto(url);
await page.click('[data-testid="submit"]');
await page.fill('[name="email"]', 'user@example.com');
const text = await page.innerText('article');
await browser.close();
```

### CDP
```typescript
import CDP from 'chrome-remote-interface';
const client = await CDP({ port: 9222 });
const { Page, Runtime } = client;
await Page.navigate({ url });
await Page.loadEventFired();
const { result } = await Runtime.evaluate({
  expression: `(${extractArticle.toString()})()`,
  returnByValue: true
});
```

### Selector Priority
`data-testid` > `aria-label` > `role` > `text` > `CSS class` > `XPath`

## Form Filling

```typescript
function detectFormFields() {
  return [...document.querySelectorAll('input, select, textarea')].map(el => ({
    label: el.closest('label')?.textContent?.trim() || el.placeholder || el.name,
    selector: el.id ? `#${el.id}` : `[data-testid="${el.dataset.testid}"]`,
    type: el.type
  }));
}

function fillForm(data: Record<string, string>) {
  for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(data)) {
    const el = document.querySelector(`[name="${key}"], [data-testid="${key}"]`) as HTMLInputElement;
    if (el) {
      el.value = value;
      el.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
    }
  }
}
```

## Skill Routing from Web Content

```typescript
const WEB_ROUTES = [
  { skill: 'sota-survey', keywords: ['survey', 'literature', 'review', 'papers'] },
  { skill: 'research-question', keywords: ['research question', 'hypothesis', 'contribution'] },
  { skill: 'c4-model', keywords: ['architecture', 'system diagram', 'c4'] },
  { skill: 'ddd-core', keywords: ['domain driven', 'bounded context', 'ddd'] },
  { skill: 'python-development', keywords: ['python', 'fastapi', 'pydantic'] },
  { skill: 'javascript-typescript', keywords: ['javascript', 'typescript', 'react'] },
  { skill: 'security-analysis', keywords: ['security', 'vulnerability', 'owasp'] },
  { skill: 'docker-containerization', keywords: ['docker', 'container', 'dockerfile'] },
  { skill: 'kubernetes-orchestration', keywords: ['kubernetes', 'k8s', 'pod'] },
  { skill: 'business-product-leadership', keywords: ['product strategy', 'jtbd', 'mvp'] },
];

function routeFromContent(text: string) {
  const lower = text.toLowerCase();
  return WEB_ROUTES
    .filter(r => r.keywords.some(k => lower.includes(k)))
    .map(r => r.skill)
    .slice(0, 3);
}
```

## Integration with kinhluan/skills

### Fetch from Raw GitHub
```typescript
const RAW = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kinhluan/skills/main/.agent-skills';
const skills = await fetch(`${RAW}/../skills.json`).then(r => r.json());
const skillMd = await fetch(`${RAW}/router/SKILL.md`).then(r => r.text());
```

### Parse Frontmatter
```typescript
function parseFrontmatter(md: string) {
  const m = md.match(/^---\n([\s\S]*?)\n---\n([\s\S]*)$/);
  if (!m) throw new Error('Missing frontmatter');
  return { yaml: m[1], body: m[2].trim() };
}
```

## Security Checklist
- [ ] `activeTab` > broad host permissions
- [ ] No remote script injection
- [ ] Sanitize DOM data: `text.replace(/[<>]/g, '').replace(/\s+/g, ' ').slice(0, 8000)`
- [ ] Use `chrome.scripting.executeScript` with functions (not string eval)
- [ ] CSP: `connect-src 'self' https://raw.githubusercontent.com`

